g of despair...</span><hr size=1> There is no place for me to go; no place of comfort or refuge.  I have no fortress... I look... I constantly search, but am met only by the cold desolate darkness that is my life. The only ray of light is the Book that I constantly carry with me. The One who’s message it contains, seems far away... so far that I sometimes wonder if He’s left me. Is He so disappointed in me that He can't bear to watch me stumble through this life that he gave me? Does He regret the joy with which he let me live? Or instead... have I left Him? Have I strayed away from His warm embrace into this cold desolate place... am I doomed to wonder aimlessly about with no comfort or guidance? NO HELP? Have I unknowingly run away form His presence... from the one Thing in which I know I can find strength? How do I return? <br>
<br>
I pray... I ask... I plead aloud for some kind of guidance... and receive no reply... all is still; not even the distant sound of a cricket to assure me that I'm not completely ALONE. All is quite... the only sound is the quit, quiet beating of my heart as my soul screams for some kind of answer... some kind of advice. Am I in the wrong? Are my thoughts, my ideals, my FEELINGS all a deceitful ploy of the devil to pull me farther and farther into this dark muck? No one is on my side; no one understands or even dares to comprehend my situation or the circumstances surrounding it... and of course, they don't want to... I'm so tired of being wrong, not because I am, but because that’s all I ever hear. If I am wrong about this... what I feel... what I know in my heart, something help us all because there is NO God.<br>
<br>
I know I'm not wrong and no matter how far away He seems... God is with me. Even in this cold, dark, desolate cage... He’s here. He’s the one who keeps me going... He’s the reason I haven't screamed out to the Devil in surrender, &quot;I GIVE UP!!!&quot; God Is With Me... He has to be... He promised He would be and no matter how lonely I feel... I can have the assurance that He is near. <br>
<br>
All I can do is pray... pray for the guidance and reassurance I so desperately need... and hope that this darkness... this despair will someday turn into light. I can only hope that I will someday wake up into a world full of warmth and love, where all is clear and the road ahead... as narrow as it may be beckons me happily to follow...to run hard after my Goal. I pray that when it is all said and done... when the last page of my life is read that the Reader will close the book with a smile on His face and say, &quot;Well done my good and faithful servant. Come, dine... and dwell with me FOREVER.&quot;<br>
